Aneesh Chopra, the federal government's first Chief Technology Officer (CTO), is leaving his position. President Obama praised Chopra's work in bringing the government into the 21st century and engaging the American people through technology. Some of his accomplishments include implementing electronic health records for veterans, expanding broadband access in rural communities, and modernizing government records. The President expressed his gratitude for Chopra's service and believes his leadership and innovation will have a lasting impact on Americans.